text: We were living out in the forest In a small farming mountain community   our place was about 8 miles up the mountains past last ranch about 9 pm ..my 2 sons and I were watching a movie then theres a knock on the door ,,,      Its a guy from down the valley and says do you guys know about the fire behind you ...man when I stepped outside it sounded like a 747 was roaring beside us .....      I quickly to a short drive... It was windy as hell ...about a mile up behind the house there was the fire bearing down on us the flames were candling 50 feet above the trees .    It looked like a Tsunami of fire just an enormous wall off flames throwing huge plumes of glowing ambers into the night sky ...lighting spot fires in front of the fire     I raced back and we started packing up and just about to flee .when the fire fighters started arriving ..they brought 2 huge inflatable reservoirs  and a water tanker making runs to fill them up within an hour there was 30 guys there they had sprinklers on and around the house ...and around that ...put a pump in the creek behind the house ..    the Idea was to cause a humidity bubble and the fire would go over us ....the fire fighters were gonna stay the night  so we  did too ....    Come first light the choppers started dropping fire retardant on and in front of the fire ... by that day they had over 100 men on it ..and started bringing machinery in ...    Well in the end they saved our home . and us .I have so much thanks and respect for the Brave men that fight the wild fires ....Thank you Jade Mine Fire Lillooet B.C.  https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/wildfire-blazes-northwest-of-lillooet/article1389326/
author: Albert Mag
